# RuneForged UI Rules

## UI boundaries
- UI scripts should present and coordinate data, not own core gameplay rules.
- Prefer formatter or helper utilities for tooltip text and display logic.
- Keep inventory, equipment, tooltip, and hotbar UI logic decoupled from low-level item generation rules.

## UX stability
- Preserve existing controls, focus flow, and input behavior unless explicitly asked to change them.
- Handle null or missing data safely in UI code.
- Avoid crashing UI refresh paths because of missing item or state references.

## Output requirements
- After UI changes, list:
  - required node names,
  - required exported references,
  - required signals,
  - any theme or scene assumptions.